---
description: Testing discipline, enforced on every task regardless of file type.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Testing (always applies)

- Never call a change "done" without a passing test that would fail if the change
  were reverted. If you can't write one, say so explicitly rather than skipping it.
- New backend endpoint or service method → unit test + integration test in the same PR.
- New UI component/screen with logic → component/unit test. New user-facing flow →
  one e2e test, not one per component.
- Never weaken a test to make it pass (loosening an assertion, adding a sleep to
  hide a race, catching an exception just to swallow it). Fix the code or flag the
  test as wrong and say why.
- Run the relevant test suite before declaring a task complete. Report the actual
  result, not an assumption that it passed.
